                            <comment id="15431781" author="vrodionov" created="Mon, 22 Aug 2016 23:22:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=tedyu&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;tedyu&quot;&gt;Ted Yu&lt;/a&gt;, what do you think?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15431788" author="yuzhihong@gmail.com" created="Mon, 22 Aug 2016 23:30:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-15128&quot; title=&quot;Disable region splits and merges switch in master&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-15128&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-15128&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; takes care of region normalizer already, right ?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15431824" author="vrodionov" created="Tue, 23 Aug 2016 00:03:02 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yes, you are right if splits/merges disabled normalizer won&apos;t work? What about catalog janitor?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15431863" author="vrodionov" created="Tue, 23 Aug 2016 00:29:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Nope. It seems Region normalizer sends request directly to RSRpcServices and has no idea about &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-15128&quot; title=&quot;Disable region splits and merges switch in master&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-15128&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-15128&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.  &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=tedyu&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;tedyu&quot;&gt;Ted Yu&lt;/a&gt;, can you double check that? cc: &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=hengchu&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;hengchu&quot;&gt;Heng Chu&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Another question on &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-15128&quot; title=&quot;Disable region splits and merges switch in master&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-15128&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-15128&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Do HBase region balancer and catalog janitor have an idea about disabled splits/merges? Not sure if they do splits/merges though.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; Upd: seems OK. RS report Master on every region state transition and Master allows or disallows this transition? Correct?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
